By far the the best day of vacation.
Special shout-out to @capt_jumby95 and @islandboy946 who were the absolute dream boating/snorkeling team. Iguana island was pretty cool too. 🤙🏼 Turks is the best. 💘

#cocoincashmere #turksandcaicos
Tonight was a 10/10 from ambiance to food to company 🥰

My Turks roundup of where we ate, what we ate and which activities we partook in. I love this place so. 🫶🏻

@caicos_cafe_restaurant—loved the lobster salad and lobster fra diavlo. 

@cocobistrotci—the lobster spring rolls for the table, spicy salmon on crispy rice and miso marinated salmon. 

Seven restaurant at @sevenstarsresort—always one of our favorite meals that never disappoints and feels like fine dining. Loved the tuna done two ways appetizer and the lobster bowl. 

The Terrace On Grace Bay—an easy menu and right on the main drag in a cool little modern setting. We picked up food from here one night and ate in the hotel bc we were all exhausted. 

Infiniti at @gracebayclub—I don’t normally love octopus and I loved the octopus appetizer. The sashimi and miso cod were delish. 

Bay Bistro— the two must orders for the table are conch wontons and coffee rubbed tuna (which is like a carpaccio). 

Grace’s Cottage— can’t believe I participated in eating escargot, but I did, and really enjoyed it. The burrata app was also delish, and I ordered snapper (first time having this fish). This was our first time here and is a new fave. 

The Spa at @sevenstarsresort- Coco and I got massages (our tradition), Swedish and deep tissue. This is one of the most zen spaces and the massages really are excellent. 

We booked an afternoon boating adventure through @capt_jumby95 and @islandboy946 (our new local friends whom I cannot recommend enough). We snorkeled, went to Iguana Island 🦎 and had an absolute blast hanging on the boat. 

Right in town we found the cutest icecream and coffee shop, and home and trinket shops. This was a good little afternoon escape when we wanted a reprieve from the sun. 

On that note, @gracebayclub has a well curated little gift shop called Coco, filled with familiar and unfamiliar brands. They have cute kids items too. There’s a Coco in town as well. 

Coco and I went tubing, which was a 15 minute adventure (you really don’t need longer than that anyway). 

 If I’m missing any fan faves, please let me know! 

#cocoincashmere #turksandcaicos #happyplace

Even a stylist’s closet can get to that breaking point 😂
Here’s how I cleaned up my act + some tips I’m sharing with you! 🪄 

• Remove all plastic from the dry cleaners and transfer the wire hangers to felt 

• Store the shoes in boxes that you aren’t wearing regularly (for me it’s my formal ones) 

• Line your shoes up toe/heel toe max space (you’ll get an extra pair in there!)

• Stuff your bags with tissue (I always keep the original packaging) 

• Store your bags in the original dust bags (I didn’t adhere to this for years bc I’m a visual person, but it does seem to be best for the life of the bags!)

• Display your sunnies on acrylic nail polish shelves (thank you @imagine.it.done for this tip!)

#cocoincashmere #fashionstylist #closetcleanout

Here’s the new way I’ll be doing my liner from now on thanks to @chantemakeup! 👋🏻 
Since having my makeup done I’ve gotten so many requests for how she did the liner (this was actually the reason I asked her to come over!). The key is using a gel eyeliner (this one’s from @bobbibrown) and a flat brush and really getting in there! I bought the brown and black versions of the liner so I have options. You also want to start painting the liner on from the outside to the inside and then doing the same underneath the upper lid on the lash line. 
I hope this helps and I know I’ll be watching this countless times till I master it! 🖊️

A little Friday Hermès porn for you 🤩

Truth is, I didn’t know I was a Chypre girl (pronounced sheep-ruh, had to google that one) until I asked to see “the H sandals with the strap across them” at my leather appt. in Paris. My girl came back with my dream pair. They’re SO comfy, and of course, even less $ in Europe. I didn’t buy them off the bat (bc I didn’t want to be a pig with the bag and all), and then deeply regretted my decision. The next two days the boutiques were closed for Christmas so I had to wait until the 26th. I snagged a black pair (the only one in my size) at the nearby boutique but still had this color combo stuck in my head. Colette and I went on an adventure later on that day and went back to the boutique I got my bag at and asked to see all the Chypre in my size. The sales associate came back with a brown two toned pair and an orange two toned pair. At that point I was going to swap the black I bought for the orange because it was something unique (and I can always get a cool black sandal). I begged to have him check one last time for the blue and green combo and he came back with what he thought was similar but not them (the pic I showed him has the green appear more yellow than green so he was confused). I hugged him and squealed that he found my shoes 🤣 I swapped the black leather for this pair, but am kind of kicking myself for not keeping both (he said you’re not supposed to be allowed to buy more than one but he’d let me). I DID go into Hermès in Barca just for kicks to see what colors they had and they were completely sold out. Long story short, I’m now a Chypre believer!
